HEADWORD: Fleuron
<hw>Fleu`ron"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. OF.
<ets>floron</ets>. Cf. <er>Floroon</er>.]</ety> <def>A flower-shaped
ornament, esp. one terminating an object or forming one of a series, as
a knob of a cover to a dish, or a flower-shaped part in a
necklace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

